# Accounts – Inv Ecosystem

Financial / custody / capital **accounts** (bank, broker, cash) with **holdings** and **asset-class allocation** across accounts. First business feature — **v0.1**.

See also:
- `.cursor/project/glossary.mdc` — Account vs User vs Profile
- `.cursor/project/roadmap.mdc` — v0.1 scope & priorities
- `.cursor/project/architecture.mdc` — layer rules
- `.cursor/database-supabase.mdc` — migrations, types, RLS

## Product decisions (v0.1)

| Topic | Decision |
|-------|----------|
| **Account types** | Bank, broker, cash |
| **Holdings vs positions** | Same concept — use **Holdings** in code/UI; do not model separate “positions” entity unless requirements change |
| **Allocation view** | By **asset class** (equities, bonds, cash, …) aggregated across accounts |
| **Account list fields** | Name, provider, total value, currency |
| **User ↔ account access** | v0.1 via Supabase **`app_metadata`** (which account IDs a user may access). Join table + admin UI later. |
| **Data sources** | Manual/seed in Supabase + **sync job stub** for future provider APIs (KBC, BNP, Saxo, DEGIRO, …) |
| **CRUD** | Read-only in UI for v0.1 |
| **Presentation layer** | **Yes** — filter sensitive fields before UI |
| **Sensitive fields** | Internal UUIDs, sync/API tokens, provider external IDs / account numbers |

